<subSubSection id="9F11DCC8615D91A482DA59C11830CD40" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6B3C00F43791CF284182E80AC7B4154B" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9522EBC9C309CF5E70F6DB6D1A4A95C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Colombia, Venezuela, Guyana, Bolivia, Argentina and Brazil (states of Roraima, Mato Grosso, Mato Grosso do Sul and Minas Gerais).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D0C9BFA836E04E038F2740012E9C980" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph id="3B87937454088338AEB6F687B2565FB8" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8EB6F5A68B457A234D9F30142C9ED872" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Due to the impossibility of finding the type specimen(s?) of 
<taxonomicName id="3D7901B9596158130C17601DAC24FA69" class="Globothalamea" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Reussia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Reussia triflora" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="triflora">
<emphasis id="B9F9A7CDC07599FC5359B5F9C8536F59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Reussia triflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in any of the visited herbaria, we do not designate any types for this name at this point.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9011C20A2F9A2B157F8A41B3F105F0C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="taxonomical notes">
<paragraph id="78D90EEBBFE18A4A0C70C3E852DAA58D" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Taxonomical notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE8471E670B02ACD6059A7FBC3D38819" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName id="5ABA2A9542ADF106C3F76EA312A0AA2A" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Pontederia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pontederia triflora" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triflora">
<emphasis id="6D912A1E9B4C9FE7FC980E42704E8CB4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Pontederia triflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been greatly confused with 
<taxonomicName id="AD65C87429E4F6A6AC10FEDF0F187230" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. subovata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="subovata">
<emphasis id="1EEEEA24117D84CE477841A57B5FDB75" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. subovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since its original description as 
<taxonomicName id="1CA5D5E57FC059B94A66CA7AE33E4318" genus="R." lsidName="R. triflora" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="triflora">
<emphasis id="E8C55EB1C74E9199C5BAF524BE207B52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">R. triflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="11F906C6B763F88D176C4D1D13A08D1D" author="Seubert, MA" editor="Martius, CFP" journalOrPublisher="III, part 1). Leipzig aput Frid. Fleischer, Munich" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="85 - 96" refId="B91" refString="Seubert, MA, 1847. Pontederiaceae. In: Martius, CFP, Ed., Flora Brasiliensis (Vol. III, part 1). Leipzig aput Frid. Fleischer, Munich: 85 - 96" title="Pontederiaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis (Vol." year="1847">Seubert (1847)</bibRefCitation>
. Both species share similar habit, leaf and floral morphology. Nonetheless, in 
<taxonomicName id="1D39EBAA5853A7E697C6E912A0225DB3" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. triflora" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="triflora">
<emphasis id="D54827CB81E6D73D06A475B7B9DA0145" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. triflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the petiolate leaf-blades are linear-lanceolate to linear-elliptic or linear rhomboid (vs. emergent and elliptic to narrowly ovate to ovate or subrhomboid in 
<taxonomicName id="F83B58702EB4FE90D632EA032BEC4C25" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. subovata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="subovata">
<emphasis id="531C89877117873C20D31408AA88FD97" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. subovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the inflorescences are 2
<normalizedToken id="12964FB6CCF960CF0BE3D346540BB23B" originalValue="–4(–">-4(-</normalizedToken>
5)-flowered [vs. (6
<normalizedToken id="B12BB7C34B8C86B9C6FC61BBE21BB7E9" originalValue="–)8–">-)8-</normalizedToken>
20-flowered]. Thus, we reaffirm 
<taxonomicName id="F6E58D566FC648B14FBCCCD1293FA857" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. triflora" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="triflora">
<emphasis id="9142754373F399FB5DB79F4BB180FDA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. triflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an accepted name, distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="B6A37878F6786302357CC45DA1C20383" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. subovata" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="subovata">
<emphasis id="DA418037506FF4E3345F277F5FAE6F9D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">P. subovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
